<br>
I would imagine Worry was using the new-with-PoP lvl 62 lure based (-30 resist adjustment) AE dot/slow, the lvl 57 AE poisen-resist dot/magic resist debuff, and the lvl 2 AE dot.  All of those are string based, so (s)he would have been able to use a decent lute to increase the damage and the magic resist debuff.  As for doing this with multiple bards, of those three probably the 57 doesn't stack, but the other two ought to fall under the new dot stacking rules.  Could probably sub in one of our other lower level AE dots to replace it for the additional bards.<br>
